# /internal/interpreted: Symbol provider for template access

This directory contains the generated symbol files that allow your Piko templates to access Go code from your application packages.

---

## What is this for?

Piko uses a Go interpreter to execute Go code within your template files in interpreted mode. To make your application's Go packages (like `pkg/dto`, `pkg/domain`, etc.) available to your templates, you need to generate symbol files that the interpreter can use.

The `provider.go` file in this directory imports and exposes these symbols to the Piko templating engine.

---

## Generating symbol files

Whenever you add new packages or modify the exported functions, types, or methods in your application, you need to regenerate the symbol files.

### Command

Run the following command from the root of your project to generate symbol files for all packages you want to access in your templates:

```bash
go run piko.sh/piko/internal/interp/interp_adapters/driver_symbols_extract -name interpreted \
  {{ .ModuleName }}/pkg/dto \
  {{ .ModuleName }}/pkg/domain \
  {{ .ModuleName }}/pkg/dal
```

### What does this do?

-   **`extract`**: Tells the tool to analyse the specified packages and generate symbol files.
-   **`-name interpreted`**: Names the generated symbols with the `interpreted` prefix, matching the package name in this directory.
-   **Package paths**: Lists all the Go packages you want to make available to your templates. Add or remove packages as needed for your application.

### Example with a real module path

If your module path is `github.com/mycompany/myapp`, the command would be:

```bash
go run piko.sh/piko/internal/interp/interp_adapters/driver_symbols_extract -name interpreted \
  github.com/mycompany/myapp/pkg/dto \
  github.com/mycompany/myapp/pkg/domain \
  github.com/mycompany/myapp/pkg/dal
```

---

## When to regenerate

You should regenerate your symbol files:

-   After adding new exported functions, types, or constants to your packages.
-   After changing the signature of exported functions.
-   After adding a new package that you want to access from your templates.
-   If you encounter "symbol not found" errors when running your templates.

---

## Adding more packages

To make additional packages available to your templates, simply add them to the extract command:

```bash
go run piko.sh/piko/internal/interp/interp_adapters/driver_symbols_extract -name interpreted \
  {{ .ModuleName }}/pkg/dto \
  {{ .ModuleName }}/pkg/domain \
  {{ .ModuleName }}/pkg/dal \
  {{ .ModuleName }}/pkg/auth \
  {{ .ModuleName }}/pkg/utils
```

The generated files will automatically be included when your application builds.
